('node', 'page', '0', '2', '2', 'und', '0', 'Trips\r\nCreate trips and see where other travellers are heading.\r\n\r\n<a href="/blog">Blogs</a>\r\nCreate your own blog posts, surf lots of other member blogs.\r\n\r\nChat -> http://drupal.org/project/chatroom - <a href="http://drupal.org/node/904006">waiting for D7 version</a>\r\nTalk to the crowd, live on the ajax chat.\r\n\r\nShop -> http://drupal.org/project/spreadshirt - module inactive\r\nLooking for a present or souvenirs? Get nice items with BeWelcome logo in the shop!\r\n\r\nGallery\r\nUpload your pictures, create albums and integrate them in your blog and your profile.\r\nhttp://drupal.org/project/views_gallery is a good solution - http://drupal.org/node/651114\r\n\r\nForum\r\nGet the latest information and discuss travel plans with other members.\r\n\r\nGroups\r\nFind or create groups to share your ideas with likeminded people.\r\n* og open D7 issues: http://drupal.org/project/issues/og?text=&status=Open&priorities=All&categories=All&version=7.x&component=All\r\n\r\nWiki\r\nAdd, edit or correct wiki pages. It is your BeWelcome wiki. Please help us to extend the content.\r\n* for now: <a href="http://couchwiki.org/">couchwiki</a>\r\n', '', 'filtered_html'),
('node', 'page', '0', '3', '3', 'und', '0', '<h2>Meet locals worldwide</h2> \r\nBeWelcome is a culture crossing network that lets you share a place to sleep, meet up and help others on their way. Let us show you how!\r\n\r\nThis is a test site for porting BeWelcome to Drupal.\r\nSee also http://couchwiki.org/en/Migrating_BeWelcome_to_Drupal', '', 'full_html'),
('node', 'blog', '0', '4', '4', 'und', '0', 'Moving from user fields to <a href="http://drupal.org/project/profile2">profile2</a>. Several reasons:\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Exportable into Features</li>\r\n<li>Separation between my preferences and my profile</li>\r\n<li>Possibility to have multiple profiles per user (possibly also profiles that can be controlled by more users in the future)</li>\r\n<li>Private fields</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\nSo your existing user field data has disappeared or is about to disappear any moment...', '', 'filtered_html'),
('node', 'blog', '0', '5', '5', 'und', '0', '"More earthy, more casual, less shiny, (less polished)."\r\nThis would be the direction that I would like to see for the site design, use of color, mood, etc.\r\nSome more structure in columns would be nice too, having some visible or invisible lines that guide the placement of boxes, text etc.\r\nAnd: Content should always have more visual weight than decoration, borders and labels.\r\n\r\nI''m totally not saying these should be the definitive guidelines for design guys. After all, I am not a designer at all. But as the start of a discussion, I think it''s ok.\r\n\r\n<blockquote>If a carpet looks too clean and expensive, noone dares to walk on it.</blockquote>\r\nthat was myself, but looks nice as a quote doesn''t it :)\r\n\r\nExamples:\r\n<a href="http://casarobino.org">Casa Robino</a>\r\nRight amount of casual + earthy. Green is a nice color for a site like this, and it''s not too much of it. It has a decent structure (sidebar on the right, text aligned in a good way). Headlines get the visual weight they deserve. Horizontal separation lines are placed where necessary, but they are subtle enough to not drain attention.\r\n\r\n<a href="http://couchsurfing.org">Couchsurfing</a>\r\nEarthy colors, casual look, placement of boxes follows some invisible lines but not too rigid.\r\nMood: The happiness from the picture with the red inflated couch and the profile pics on the front page is far too obtrusive.\r\n\r\nBartik theme (currently active on bw.guaka.org)\r\nIt does not exactly look beautiful, a bit too technical, dull and boring. But at least it''s not too shiny, not too polished, and has a decent structure of sidebar and text positioning.\r\nProbably we will say goodbye to the blue some day.\r\n\r\nAny thoughts?', '', 'filtered_html'),
('node', 'blog', '0', '6', '6', 'und', '0', 'I just came across some interesting <a href="http://www.istos.it/category/blog-tags/drupal-entities">blog posts about Entities</a>, a concept new in Drupal 7, which opens up a lot of new possibilities.\r\n\r\nFrom part 2:\r\n<blockquote>\r\nSo the first thing Drupal entities are is means to streamline how we deal with the basic Drupal "stuff" of nodes, comments, terms and users.\r\nNow comes the really interesting part to people that don''t worry so much about how the core of Drupal does things.\r\n\r\n1. You can define your own entities that plug into the whole Drupal way of doing stuff.\r\n2. Any entity can have fields attached to it.\r\n</blockquote>\r\n\r\nAnd something we''ll want here once it''s ready:\r\n<blockquote>\r\nThe team over at Examiner.com use entities to store user profile revisioning information (functionality they are hoping to release soon).\r\n</blockquote>\r\n\r\nThrough this I also stumbled upon http://drupal.org/project/relation, which is probably useful for implementing friendship links and comments here.\r\n\r\nFinally, the word is out, Drupal 7 will be released on January 5th.  Since many module developers have pledged to have a D7 release of their module we''ll be able to get a better idea of where we''re at with this project.', '', 'filtered_html'),
('node', 'blog', '0', '7', '7', 'und', '0', 'The BW developers mailing list is not working properly now.  I just found Matthias'' post and thought it could be good to take his questions here in the meanwhile.\r\n\r\n<blockquote>I have some questions about the BW-Drupal migration: Will it be possible to port all of the current content from BW to the Drupal based site? Do we need to port everything?</blockquote>\r\n\r\nIt will be possible to migrate all content.  It might have different degrees of difficulties.  Andreas and I have just finished a project to migrate a big .asp site (with a lot of static content in .asp files) and our experience with that will come in pretty handy. We''ll probably take a different approach, using more widely utilized modules (e.g. <a href="http://drupal.org/project/tw">Table Wizard</a> and <a href="http://drupal.org/project/data">Data</a>, see also <a href="http://drupal.org/node/580650">How Data relates to Table Wizard</a>).\r\n\r\n<blockquote>\r\nFeatures like trips, blogs or chat are rarely used, but on the other hands\r\nit would not be fair to the users if we delete their content.\r\n</blockquote>\r\n\r\nWe should try to migrate everything but if there is only a little bit of content we might have to inform users and ask them about their opinion.  If it''s really only a little bit of content we could even migrate things manually.\r\n\r\nNote that efforts towards data migration should be delayed until we have a proper proof of concept where the basic functionality is in place.\r\n\r\n<blockquote>\r\nWhat about translations? There were many people who invested their freetime\r\nto translate the website into many different languages. Their effort\r\nshouldn''t be in vain.\r\n</blockquote>\r\n\r\nTranslations are essential and we will make a big effort to migrate the results into Drupal - where it makes sense.  Drupal and many often used modules (e.g. Views) are already very well translated and we should try to build with this where it makes sense.  So quite a few translation strings won''t be migrated since they''re already available in Drupal.  On the other hand, it will be great to find a way to feed BW translation efforts back into the bigger Drupal ecosphere.\r\n\r\n<blockquote>\r\nWhere are the biggest challenges in the Drupal migration?\r\n</blockquote>\r\n\r\nI see the biggest challenge in keeping up momentum and finding a way to collaborate.  For example, I had given more people admin rights in order to achieve this but then later realized this is a mistake since it''s hard to keep track of what''s going on.  So the first hurdle is to divide the project into chunks that will allow people to work on their preferred parts.  For now this is limited to the theme I think, as long as we''re with Bartik on this main install the theme is the most harmless part.\r\n', '', 'filtered_html'),
('node', 'page', '0', '8', '8', 'und', '0', '<h2>The idea</h2> \r\n \r\n<div class="subcolumns"> \r\n  <div class="c50l"> \r\n    <div class="subcl"> \r\n<h3>The concept</h3><p>Imagine arriving in a city like Paris or Mumbai and, instead of trying to find a taxi, there is somebody already waiting for you. Imagine that instead of going to eat at the place recommended by the guidebook, someone shows you their favourite restaurant. Imagine the experience staying as a personal guest of your new friend rather than sleeping in an impersonal hotel room. BeWelcome makes it possible.\r\n    </p><h3>You like the idea? Get active!</h3><p>Join one of our teams: share the work, the commitment and the fun! We are currently looking for:<br />\r\n<h4>People who help building the website</h4><ul><li>software developer (PHP+MySQL)</li><li>web designer ((X)HTML/CSS)</li></ul><br />\r\nGet in contact with <a href="members/philipplange">Philipp</a> or <a href="members/fake51">Peter</a><br />\r\n<br />\r\n<h4>People with writing skills</h4><ul><li> translators (Chinese, Japanese, Arabic, etc)</li></ul><br />\r\nGet in contact with <a href="members/sitarane>Julien</a> or <a href="members/ieva">Ieva</a><br />\r\n<br />\r\n<h4>People to promote BeWelcome</h4><h4>Members to start build local communities</h4></p><p>Needs content</p><h3>Your opinion, please!</h3><p>We are constantly working on the improvement of BeWelcome. If you have a suggestion, please <a href="http://www.bewelcome.org/forums">let us know</a>.</p>    </div> \r\n   </div> \r\n \r\n \r\n  <div class="c50r"> \r\n    <div class="subcr"> \r\n<h3>How is it organised?</h3><p>Dreaming alone is not enough. That''s why we have founded <a href="wiki/BeVolunteer">BeVolunteer</a>, a non-profit organisation registered in Rennes, France. Through BeVolunteer''s official statutes, we provide a basis for democratic decision making, financial transparency and information security so that we can protect our members and manage the project BeWelcome effectively.<br />\r\n<br />\r\n</p><h3 class="first" ><a href="blog/tags/Community News for the frontpage">Community News</a></h3> \r\n                <div class="floatbox"> \r\n                                            <h4 class="news"><a href="blog/sitarane/677">Servas-BeWelcome update</a></h4> \r\n                        <span class="small grey">written by <a href="user/sitarane">sitarane</a> - 2010/09/30 10:51</span> \r\n                        <p> \r\n                        <p>Monday there was a meeting between the Servas-to-BeWelcome project members. It involved two members of the BW board of directors (including me), one BW coder and three Servas coordinators (including the president of Servas International).<br /><br />The topic was the general roadmap for the project. A draft had been submitted a few days earlier by one Servas coordinator and we were going to discuss it and take it to a complete state. Most of the items of the roadmap were pretty trivial and were quickly agreed upon. However we ran into a disagreement on one point. The draft included the option...</p>                        </p> \r\n                                            <h4 class="news"><a href="blog/fake51/626">BeWelcome server updates</a></h4> \r\n                        <span class="small grey">written by <a href="user/fake51">fake51</a> - 2010/01/30 18:33</span> \r\n                        <p> \r\n                        It''s been stated a couple of times on the forum and possibly written about in some forum posts: BeWelcome is relocating it''s test server to one of it''s members (Tobixen - many thanks!). In connection with this, you might experience some problems if you try to reach the old BV wiki or the trac pages (if you''re trying to put in a bug report). Things should be up and running within a day or two again, though - so please, don''t worry too much if you see some pages broken, they should be fixed again soon.                        </p> \r\n                    \r\n                    <a href="blog/tags/Community News for the frontpage">Read more</a> \r\n    </div> \r\n  </div> ', '', 'full_html'),
('node', 'blog', '0', '9', '9', 'und', '0', 'See <a href="http://drupal.org/node/1007286">og.module on D7 - how to join a group?</a> on drupal.org\r\n\r\n<blockquote>I should add it to the README, but should find the time for it, or If you guys feel like writing a small patch...\r\n\r\nIn short -- enable og-ui module, and in your content type go to "display fields" and in the group field select "Group subscription" as the formatter.</blockquote>\r\n\r\nDid that. Now everyone except the group author can subscribe or unsubscribe.\r\n\r\nIs this enough for us?\r\nSee <a href="http://drupal.org/node/1006348">Make group memberships fieldable.</a> on drupal.org\r\n\r\n<blockquote>I''m not very clear on the issue. Currently there is a single field that is responsible for subscription, which uses field API. This field''s name is hardcoded and is important, so we can keep track using this name what entity/ bundle is a group or a group post.</blockquote>', '', 'filtered_html'),
('node', 'blog', '0', '10', '10', 'und', '0', 'I set up a <a href="http://drupal.org/project/views">View</a> to <a href="/list-members">list all members</a> - not that we have so many here, but I thought it was nice to fill in some menu links quickly.\r\n\r\nWhen I wanted to increase the number of items shown on the first page I ran into an issue.  I <a href="http://drupal.org/node/994856">copied the error into a d.o bug report for Views</a>.  Within 6 hours dereine replied that he had committed a fix (to cvs).\r\n\r\nI don''t like CVS so I decided to wait for <a href="http://drupal.org/">d.o</a> to come up with a new Views 7.x-3.x-dev package and today I fetched that (with <a href="http://drupal.org/project/drush">drush dl</a>, since drush up is not working properly on this install now).  Problem solved - for us and also for the 100000s of other websites that will be using D7 Views.', '', 'filtered_html'),
('node', 'blog', '0', '11', '11', 'und', '0', 'I drush upped.  Which means I upgraded all modules and core to Drupal 7.0-rc4.  I also found that og has an alpha release now for D7, so I drush dl''d that.\r\n\r\nIf you haven''t tried drush yet: go get it, it''s awesome.  It''s a <a href="http://drupal.org/project/drush">DRUpal SHell</a>, which means you get tons of power at your fingertips, saving you hours of time fetching modules, clearing cache, running cron, going into a Drupal database, executing PHP stuff from a Drupal site environment and much more.', '', 'filtered_html'),
('node', 'page', '0', '12', '12', 'und', '0', 'This Drupal installation is an attempt at moving BeWelcome to Drupal.  You can sign up here and help out with the creation and migration process.  You will also find regular updates here about our progress. Check and edit <a href="http://couchwiki.org/en/Migrating_BeWelcome_to_Drupal">this page on Couchwiki for a messy overview of the migration</a>.  We''re also posting blog posts with mostly technical status updates and discussions.\r\n\r\n<strong><em>This is not the most recent version of BW Drupal. Check http://gitorious.org/bw-drupal for that</em></strong>', '', 'filtered_html'),
('node', 'blog', '0', '13', '13', 'und', '0', 'Sitting in our living room in Brussels with <a href="http://benn.org/">Meinhard</a> and <a href="http://triphopping.com/">Kenny</a>.  Hopefully good stuff will come out :)\r\n\r\nI''ll be updating this post as we go.\r\n\r\nSome past activity:\r\n- Friday evening Meinhard managed to set up BW on Drupal during the train ride from Hamburg.\r\n- Thursday night Kenny got an introduction to Drupal and is very interested in migrating Triphopping to Drupal.\r\n- https://gitorious.org/bw-drupal\r\n- think about what to do at http://www.bewelcome.org/wiki/Berlin_summer_camp\r\n\r\n<h2>General issues</h2>\r\nSome problems we see with current BeWelcome:\r\n- login? easy login => openid (also allows for google and yahoo openid)\r\n- usability\r\n-- forum is a mess usability-wise\r\n-- profiles (profile pic should open bigger pic, not gallery with smaller pic, "difficult to upload pics")\r\n\r\n<h2>what needs to be migrated?</h2>\r\n', '', 'filtered_html'),
('node', 'page', '0', '14', '14', 'und', '0', '<h4>1. Registration</h4> \r\n<p>By registering with BeWelcome and creating your profile, you agree to provide accurate, up-to-date and complete information about yourself. You further agree that you will ensure that this information is kept accurate and up to date at all times. This is especially important with respect to your email address, since that is the primary way in which we will communicate with you about your account. If you fail to follow this rule, we reserve the right to edit, close and/or delete your account and profile and thereby remove any information and prevent you from using the site.\r\nAs part of the registration process, you will designate a password, subject to our password security requirements. It is your responsibility to keep this password confidential. If you find out that your password or account is being used by someone without your consent, or you discover any other breach of security, you agree to notify us promptly without delay.</p> \r\n \r\n<h4>2. Privacy</h4> \r\n<p>We are committed to safeguarding your privacy. Thus we understand your wish and respect your right to privacy and personal information. However, by submitting your photograph and any other personal information, you allow any member of BeWelcome to view and use this information. If you do not wish to keep your personal picture or information private vis-&agrave;-vis other members of BeWelcome, you shall choose to hide it accordingly. We reserve the right to collect further personal information from you that we do not post on BeWelcome. Under normal circumstances we will not transfer your personal information to unaffiliated third parties without your consent. However, we reserve the right to transfer such information without your consent in the following cases: to prevent an emergency, to protect or enforce our legal rights, to protect or enforce legal rights of a third party or in pursuance to a court order or subpoena or