('1', 'node', ' impressum anbieterkennzeichung nach 6 teledienstgesetz information provider identification according to 6 teledienstgesetz bevolunteer c o jeanyves hegron 19 rue de paris 35500 vitre france  info bevolunteerorg bewelcome is the property of the bevolunteer non profit organization see bevolunteer wiki the layout is based on yaml 20052006 by dirk jesse  ', '0'),
('2', 'node', ' explore trips create trips and see where other travellers are heading blogs create your own blog posts surf lots of other member blogs chat  http drupalorg project chatroom  waiting for d7 version talk to the crowd live on the ajax chat shop  http drupalorg project spreadshirt  module inactive looking for a present or souvenirs get nice items with bewelcome logo in the shop gallery upload your pictures create albums and integrate them in your blog and your profile http drupalorg project viewsgallery is a good solution  http drupalorg node 651114 forum get the latest information and discuss travel plans with other members groups find or create groups to share your ideas with likeminded people og open d7 issues  http drupalorg project issues og text status open priorities all cat  wiki add edit or correct wiki pages it is your bewelcome wiki please help us to extend the content for now  couchwiki ', '0'),
('3', 'node', ' about ', '0'),
('4', 'node', ' profile2 admin s blog moving from user fields to profile2  several reasons exportable into features separation between my preferences and my profile possibility to have multiple profiles per user possibly also profiles that can be controlled by more users in the future private fields so your existing user field data has disappeared or is about to disappear any moment  ', '0'),
('5', 'node', '  more earthy more casual less shiny guidelines for visual appearance admin s blog  more earthy more casual less shiny less polished this would be the direction that i would like to see for the site design use of color mood etc some more structure in columns would be nice too having some visible or invisible lines that guide the placement of boxes text etc and content should always have more visual weight than decoration borders and labels i m totally not saying these should be the definitive guidelines for design guys after all i am not a designer at all but as the start of a discussion i think it s ok if a carpet looks too clean and expensive noone dares to walk on it that was myself but looks nice as a quote doesn t it examples  casa robino right amount of casual earthy green is a nice color for a site like this and it s not too much of it it has a decent structure sidebar on the right text aligned in a good way headlines get the visual weight they deserve horizontal separation lines are placed where necessary but they are subtle enough to not drain attention couchsurfing earthy colors casual look placement of boxes follows some invisible lines but not too rigid mood the happiness from the picture with the red inflated couch and the profile pics on the front page is far too obtrusive bartik theme currently active on bwguakaorg it does not exactly look beautiful a bit too technical dull and boring but at least it s not too shiny not too polished and has a decent structure of sidebar and text positioning probably we will say goodbye to the blue some day any thoughts  ', '0'),
('6', 'node', ' new in d7 entities admin s blog i just came across some interesting blog posts about entities  a concept new in drupal 7 which opens up a lot of new possibilities from part 2 so the first thing drupal entities are is means to streamline how we deal with the basic drupal stuff of nodes comments terms and users now comes the really interesting part to people that don t worry so much about how the core of drupal does things 1 you can define your own entities that plug into the whole drupal way of doing stuff 2 any entity can have fields attached to it and something we ll want here once it s ready the team over at examinercom use entities to store user profile revisioning information functionality they are hoping to release soon through this i also stumbled upon http drupalorg project relation  which is probably useful for implementing friendship links and comments here finally the word is out drupal 7 will be released on january 5th since many module developers have pledged to have a d7 release of their module we ll be able to get a better idea of where we re at with this project  ', '0'),
('7', 'node', ' matthias questions about the bwdrupal migration admin s blog the bw developers mailing list is not working properly now i just found matthias post and thought it could be good to take his questions here in the meanwhile i have some questions about the bwdrupal migration will it be possible to port all of the current content from bw to the drupal based site do we need to port everything it will be possible to migrate all content it might have different degrees of difficulties andreas and i have just finished a project to migrate a big asp site with a lot of static content in asp files and our experience with that will come in pretty handy we ll probably take a different approach using more widely utilized modules eg table wizard and data  see also how data relates to table wizard  features like trips blogs or chat are rarely used but on the other hands it would not be fair to the users if we delete their content we should try to migrate everything but if there is only a little bit of content we might have to inform users and ask them about their opinion if it s really only a little bit of content we could even migrate things manually note that efforts towards data migration should be delayed until we have a proper proof of concept where the basic functionality is in place what about translations there were many people who invested their freetime to translate the website into many different languages their effort shouldn t be in vain translations are essential and we will make a big effort to migrate the results into drupal where it makes sense drupal and many often used modules eg views are already very well translated and we should try to build with this where it makes sense so quite a few translation strings won t be migrated since they re already available in drupal on the other hand it will be great to find a way to feed bw translation efforts back into the bigger drupal ecosphere where are the biggest challenges in the drupal migration i see the biggest challenge in keeping up momentum and finding a way to collaborate for example i had given more people admin rights in order to achieve this but then later realized this is a mistake since it s hard to keep track of what s going on so the first hurdle is to divide the project into chunks that will allow people to work on their preferred parts for now this is limited to the theme i think as long as we re with bartik on this main install the theme is the most harmless part  ', '0'),
('8', 'node', ' about bewelcome ', '0'),
('9', 'node', ' how to join a group  admin s blog see ogmodule on d7 how to join a group  on drupalorg i should add it to the readme but should find the time for it or if you guys feel like writing a small patch in short enable ogui module and in your content type go to display fields and in the group field select group subscription as the formatter did that now everyone except the group author can subscribe or unsubscribe is this enough for us see make group memberships fieldable on drupalorg i m not very clear on the issue currently there is a single field that is responsible for subscription which uses field api this field s name is hardcoded and is important so we can keep track using this name what entity bundle is a group or a group post  ', '0'),
('10', 'node', ' example of how this project is improving d7 admin s blog i set up a view to list all members  not that we have so many here but i thought it was nice to fill in some menu links quickly when i wanted to increase the number of items shown on the first page i ran into an issue i copied the error into a do bug report for views  within 6 hours dereine replied that he had committed a fix to cvs i don t like cvs so i decided to wait for do to come up with a new views 7x3xdev package and today i fetched that with drush dl  since drush up is not working properly on this install now problem solved for us and also for the 100000s of other websites that will be using d7 views  ', '0'),
('11', 'node', ' drush up admin s blog i drush upped which means i upgraded all modules and core to drupal 70rc4 i also found that og has an alpha release now for d7 so i drush dl d that if you haven t tried drush yet go get it it s awesome it s a drupal shell  which means you get tons of power at your fingertips saving you hours of time fetching modules clearing cache running cron going into a drupal database executing php stuff from a drupal site environment and much more  ', '0'),
('12', 'node', ' bewelcome on drupal this drupal installation is an attempt at moving bewelcome to drupal you can sign up here and help out with the creation and migration process you will also find regular updates here about our progress check and edit this page on couchwiki for a messy overview of the migration  we re also posting blog posts with mostly technical status updates and discussions this is not the most recent version of bw drupal check http gitoriousorg bwdrupal for that ', '0'),
('13', 'node', ' bxl geekend admin s blog sitting in our living room in brussels with meinhard and kenny  hopefully good stuff will come out i ll be updating this post as we go some past activity friday evening meinhard managed to set up bw on drupal during the train ride from hamburg thursday night kenny got an introduction to drupal and is very interested in migrating triphopping to drupal  https gitoriousorg bwdrupal  think about what to do at http wwwbewelcomeorg wiki berlinsummercamp general issues some problems we see with current bewelcome login easy login openid also allows for google and yahoo openid usability forum is a mess usabilitywise profiles profile pic should open bigger pic not gallery with smaller pic difficult to upload pics what needs to be migrated  ', '0'),
('14', 'node', ' terms of use ', '0'),
('15', 'node', ' data migration foreign keys and other challenges admin s blog not long ago i had to migrate a bunch of drupal nodes from a test site to a live site this situation is not the same as ours because our original content does not live in drupal and i was on d6 still there are some things we can learn from 1 structure and completeness of imported content for whatever api functions we use 2 foreign keys and the inevitable mismatch of autoincrement ids 1 structure and completeness of imported content drupal s nodesave or entitysave api this api in d6 has some expectations on the format and completeness of data usually nested structures of associative array and vanilla stdclass objects we want to import if something is not working as expected this is a place to look 2 foreign keys a lot of the relations between db tables on bwrox site will translate into relations and references between drupal objects the structure will be different and autoincrement ids will be different if a user location on bwrox has a country id of 26 the same country might have an id of 111 on bwdrupal or it might even be a string key instead of an autoincrement id solution maintain a map of primary keys for each imported piece of content we should therefore maintain a reference to the original bwrox object this can be stored in an integervalued field or in a custom table that we have to keep up to date we then will use that map to alter the foreign key values on imported content we need to be careful with the order of things we import in some cases there might be circular dependencies so we have to keep a list of postponed foreign key updates that have to be done later if we use existing solutions for the data migration we need to find out if they are flexible enough to deal with these issues probably we will have to write some code of our own to hook into the import module at that time i used node export  which does have a nice api for exactly this purpose but as said this does only work from drupal to drupal  ', '0'),
('16', 'node', ' deadminned most users admin s blog i deadminned everyone except user 1 myself and lemonhead d7 is still a bit too volatile and you don t need admin rights to play with it instead it s easy to set up your own drupal 7 installation and eg create a first bw theme for d7 if wanted i can make the features available that i ve created so far bw user profile bw faq and bw wiki the first is the most interesting but right now it s not yet possible to export the complete user field settings only the individual fields can be exported bw faq is a little attempt at the bw s faq and bw wiki likewise for the wiki there s also a trusted role which can easily be given some more permissions if needed and i had forgotten to turn on the view user profiles permission to authenticated users that s fixed now so it s already a bit more interesting  ', '0'),
('17', 'node', ' privacy policy ', '0');
